# In Python Escape Character :-
    # # 1. \'   -> It is used to print a single quote. Example: 'It\'s nice' prints: It's nice
    # 2. \\   -> It is used to print a backslash. Example: 'A\\B' prints: A\B
    # 3. \n   -> It is used to create a new line. Example: 'Hi\nHello' prints:  Hi
                                                                        #  Hello on separate lines
    # 4. \r   -> It moves the cursor to the start of the line and overwrites old text with new text. Example: "Hello\rWorld!" prints: World!
    # 5. \t   -> It is used to add a big space (Tab). Example: 'A\tB' prints: A    B
    # 6. \b   -> It works like a backspace key and deletes the letter just before it. Example: "Hello \bWorld!" prints: HelloWorld!
    # 7. \f   -> It is used to force a page break, mostly for old printers.
    # 8. \ooo -> It creates a character using a 3-digit Octal number. Example: '\110' prints: H
    # 9. \xhh -> It creates a character using a 2-digit Hex number. Example: '\x48' prints: H
