17_if_name_main:-

    1. What is this?
    # if __name__ == "__main__":
    # A special Python statement that checks whether the file is being run directly or imported as a module.

    2. What is it useful for?
    # It prevents certain code from running when the file is imported into another program.
    # Commonly used for testing functions, running examples, or executing the main program logic.

    3. Is this necessary?
    # No but some thime, it is  mandatory.
    # Small scripts can work without it.
    # However, it is considered a good practice, especially in larger projects and reusable modules.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

18_os_Module:- 
    # getcwd() -> Returns the current working directory (current folder path).
    # chdir() -> Changes the current working directory to the specified path.
    # mkdir() -> Creates a new directory (folder).
    # makedirs() -> Creates multiple nested directories at once.
    # rmdir() -> Removes an empty directory.
    # removedirs() -> Removes nested empty directories.
    # rename() -> Renames a file or directory.
    # listdir() -> Returns a list containing the names of files and folders in a directory.
    # remove() -> Deletes a file.
    # system() -> Executes a system command in the operating system shell.
    # path.exists() -> Checks whether a file or directory exists.
    # path.isfile() -> Checks whether the specified path is a file.
    # path.isdir() -> Checks whether the specified path is a directory.
    # path.join() -> Joins one or more path components into a single path.
    # path.basename() -> Returns the final component (file/folder name) of a path.
    # path.dirname() -> Returns the directory portion of a path.
    # path.getsize() -> Returns the size of a file in bytes.
    # environ -> Provides access to environment variables as a dictionary.
    # walk() -> Traverses a directory tree and returns information about files and folders.
    # getlogin() -> Returns the name of the currently logged-in user.
    # cpu_count() -> Returns the number of CPUs available in the system.
    # copy() -> Copies a file from one location to another.
    # copy2() -> Copies a file along with its metadata (timestamps, permissions).
    # move() -> Moves a file or directory to a new location.
    # rmtree() -> Deletes a directory and all its contents.
    # make_archive() -> Creates a compressed archive (ZIP, TAR, etc.) from a directory.
    # unpack_archive() -> Extracts files from an archive.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
